Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of a Transformer base model, which is a popular model architecture in NMT research. 

The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the evaluation of NMT models on the WMT15 English-German test set, which involves natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as NLP tasks often involve image captioning and other visual tasks. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of exact inference procedures, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
